    ## Hub and Seer Concepts integration:
        [ ] Case Automation Model and the Case Automation Engine (Seer Case Automation)
        [ ] Workbench as an Agent in the Tenant Agent Registry
        [ ] Scenario as an Agent in the Tenant Agent Registry
        [ ] Avoiding Circular Loops between Agents
        [ ] How does any Scenario as an Agent different from Seer Case Automation as an Orchestrator Agent?

    ## Seer Agents and Hub Agents:
        - The application itself doesn't host 'Hub Agents'; 
        - A Seer application have 'internal agents' that are not 'hub visible'
        - A Seer Agent receives Task Assignment Webhook Call; This call is delivered to the Seer Hub Application representing the Seer Agent; 
        - The Seer Hub Application then delegates the task to the Seer Agent Engine to complete the task.        

